# {{PROJECT_NAME}} — Project Chronicle

> **The book of strategic decisions and findings — APPEND-ONLY.** One entry per completed
> task (and per strategic decision): what was done, key findings, decisions, questions
> raised/resolved, next action. Entries are added, never edited or deleted.
>
> A ticket spans many tasks; memory does not. This file keeps the reasoning. It is **cited as
> incident history** by the code-reviewer and the devils-advocate to ground their objections
> in what actually happened before. Task-level machine trace lives in
> `docs/activity_log.jsonl`; ticket status lives in the tracker; this file records only what
> changes the project's direction or carries a lesson forward.
>
> **Write at close** (`/close-task`, Step 10). Newest entries go at the bottom (append).

